Customer: This entity will store information about the customers, such as their name, contact information, and other relevant details.

Product: This entity will store information about the products that the business sells, such as the name, description, and price.

Sale: This entity will represent a single transaction between a customer and the business. It will include information about the products sold, the price, and any other relevant details.

Region: This entity will represent the geographical regions in which the business operates. It could include information such as the region name, location, and other relevant details.

Promotion: This entity will represent any promotions or marketing activities that the business is conducting. It could include information such as the name, description, and duration of the promotion.

Alert: This entity will store information about any alerts generated by the system, such as alerts for low inventory, infrequent customer purchases, or other relevant events.
